Program: Outlook
Title: The North Korean Artist Who Pokes Fun at the Regime
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p011h9fc
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 12 Dec 2012
The North Korean artist Sun Mu who defected to South Korea tells Matthew Bannister how he now parodies his former propaganda. We also meet Lonnie Bissonette, the Canadian daredevil who broke his neck jumping off a bridge and now jumps from cliffs in a wheelchair. Picture of the former North Korean Leader Kim Jong-il by Sun Mu Show less